com.badlogic.gdx.backends
Interface InputListener

public interface InputListener

An InputListener is used to receive input events from an Application. For this it has to be registered with the Application via Application.addInputListener(). These events might arrive asynchronously in a UI thread, the Application will buffer those events and invoke the methods of the listener in the rendering thread to get rid of the need to synchronize the UI and renderer thread for input. If an input listener signals that it processed an event by returning true the event will not be passed to other listeners in the listener chain (multiple InputListeners can register with an Application). Note that mouse and touch screen are equivalent here.

Author:
mzechner
